<br>
My point about confessing the faith is nothing more than a vital NT faith (Rom. 10:9-10; etc.). Lutheran theology does not separate worship from other aspects of life. And being liturgical has nothing to do with whether the church is &quot;formal&quot; or &quot;informal.&quot; If you desire I can print out the words that form the basis of our worship service. You will see that it is basically Biblical passages, some set to music, others spoken. <p>In Christ,<br>
